# Sajtmaskin Terminology

## Site layers (top to bottom)

| Layer | What it is | URL pattern |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| **Vercel** | Hosting platform. Deploys, domains, env vars, CDN. | vercel.com |
| **v0** | AI code generation platform. Generates React code, returns demoUrl. | v0.dev, *.vusercontent.net |
| **Sajtmaskin** | Our app. Orchestrates v0, manages projects, users, deploy flow. | sajtmaskin.se |
| **Demo sites** | User-generated sites. Built by v0, previewed via demoUrl, deployed to Vercel. | *.vercel.app or custom domain |

## Pages in our app

### Start page (`/`)

The landing page with 4 entry modes shown as tabs/cards:

| Mode | Code name | Component | What it does |
|------|-----------|-----------|-------------|
| **Analyserad** (Wizard) | `wizard` | `PromptWizardModalV2` | 5-step guided questionnaire that builds a detailed prompt |
| **Kategori** (Templates) | `category` | `TemplateGallery` | Browse template categories, pick a starting point |
| **Audit** | `audit` | `SiteAuditSection` + `AuditModal` | Analyze an existing website URL, show improvement suggestions |
| **Fritext** (Freeform) | `freeform` | `PromptInput` | Type a free-text description directly |

All 4 modes lead to the **builder** via `/builder?buildMethod=<mode>&...`

### Builder (`/builder`)

The main workspace where the user iterates on their site:
- Left panel: chat interface (prompt, AI responses, version history)
- Right panel: live preview (iframe showing the demoUrl from v0)
- Header: model selection, deploy button, project settings

### Admin (`/admin`)

Internal dashboard with tabs: Database, Environment, Analytics, Prompts.

## Key concepts

### Two operational lanes

When discussing generation architecture, prefer this mental model:

| Lane | What belongs here | What it is not |
|------|-------------------|----------------|
| **Runtime lane** | `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/`, scaffold matching, scaffold serialization, preview/deploy generation flow | Not the template gallery, not raw external datasets |
| **Research lane** | `research/external-templates/reference-library/`, raw discovery under `research/external-templates/raw-discovery/`, curated generated JSON in `src/lib/gen/template-library/` | Not the runtime scaffold registry |

Important rule:
- Treat the **template gallery** in `src/lib/templates/` as a product/UI discovery surface, not as a third generation lane.
- Do NOT describe the system as if runtime generation alternates between "templates" and "scaffolds". Runtime generation should be described as scaffold-driven.

### Template vs scaffold vs Vercel template

These concepts are different and should NOT be mixed:

| Term | Swedish label | Meaning | Scope |
|------|---------------|---------|-------|
| **Sajtmaskin template gallery item** | `hemsidemall`, `startmall`, or `kategori-mall` | A user-facing gallery entry from `src/lib/templates/`. Useful for browsing, filtering, and inspiration in the product UI. It is not the runtime scaffold registry. | Product/UI concept |
| **Scaffold** | `grundmall` or `starter scaffold` | An internal, code-level starter project from `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/` that the engine modifies instead of generating everything from scratch. | Internal runtime concept |
| **Vercel Template** | `extern Vercel-template` | A public starter repo from [vercel.com/templates](https://vercel.com/templates). External reference material only, not a live runtime dependency. | External ecosystem concept |
| **Curated template reference** | `kuraterad referensmall` | A normalized reference dossier or generated JSON derived from external template research, typically under `research/external-templates/reference-library/` or `src/lib/gen/template-library/`. Used to improve scaffolds, not to replace them at runtime. | Research/curation concept |
| **Reference dossier** | `referensdossier` | One curated per-template research package containing a manifest, summary, and selected file excerpts. Stored under `research/external-templates/reference-library/dossiers/`. | Research/curation concept |
| **Raw discovery** | `rå upptäckt` | Noisy local scrape/discovery output stored under `research/external-templates/raw-discovery/`. Useful for triage and audit work, not a runtime or canonical research source. | Research input concept |
| **Raw template dataset** | `rå template-dataset` | Local `_sidor`-style datasets used as build-time input for curation scripts. Richer than raw discovery but still not runtime data. | Research input concept |
| **Generated research artifact** | `genererad research-artefakt` | Committed JSON or embeddings derived from curated reference data, such as `src/lib/gen/template-library/` or `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/scaffold-research.generated.json`. | Build/runtime support concept |
| **Multi-tenant** | `delad plattform` | One codebase / one deployment serving many tenants with different data/domains. Best term for the sajtmaskin app itself. | Hosting architecture concept |
| **Multi-project** | `separata kundprojekt` | One isolated Vercel project per customer/app. Best term for generated user sites and deploy targets. | Hosting architecture concept |

Preferred terminology:
- In product copy for users: say **`hemsidemall`** or **`startmall`**
- When referring to `src/lib/templates/`: say **`template gallery`** or **`gallery item`**
- In engine/code discussions: say **`scaffold`** or **`starter scaffold`**
- When referring to Vercel's public library: explicitly say **`Vercel template`**
- When referring to normalized external research: say **`curated template reference`** or **`reference dossier`**
- When referring to noisy local scrape output: say **`raw discovery`**
- When referring to committed JSON/embeddings derived from research: say **`generated research artifacts`**

Important rule:
- Do NOT call our internal scaffolds just `templates` without qualifier, since sajtmaskin already uses `templates` for another concept.
- Do NOT call `src/lib/templates/` entries `Vercel templates` unless you explicitly mean their upstream source, not their role inside the product.
- Do NOT describe `research/external-templates/reference-library/` as a second runtime scaffold registry.
- Do NOT describe `research/external-templates/raw-discovery/` as curated research. It is intentionally noisy input.
- Do NOT imply that external reference templates are cloned into runtime generation by default. They inform prompts, embeddings, and scaffold improvements unless a separate import flow explicitly says otherwise.
- Do NOT use `multi-tenant` or `multi-project` as if they were template concepts. They describe hosting/deployment architecture, not content/category selection.

### Common chat aliases

Treat common misspellings and spoken-style aliases as canonical platform names:

| Alias in chat | Canonical term |
|---------------|----------------|
| `Varicell`, `Vericell` | `Vercel` |
| `Veenol`, `Venol` | `v0` |

When answering, prefer canonical names (`Vercel`, `v0`) even if user writes an alias.

### Orchestrator terms

Use this vocabulary consistently for automation work:

- `orchestrator run` - the full dated execution folder under `.cursor/orchestrator/run/`
- `orchestrator agent` - the coordinator that plans, delegates, validates, and performs minor fixes
- `run roadmap` - the per-run `ROADMAP.md`
- `track plan` - an intermediate tier-2 plan for one broader workstream inside an orchestrator run
- `agent log` - a per-workload execution note written by the delegated agent
- `final sweep` - the closing cleanup and audit pass for dead code, ghost routes, stale files, and doc drift

Treat `/orchestrator` and `/automation` as the compact startup aliases for the
orchestrator-run system.

### Research pipeline terms

Use this pipeline vocabulary consistently:

1. `raw discovery` -> scrape output such as `research/external-templates/raw-discovery/`
2. `raw template dataset` -> `_sidor`-style local datasets used for curation
3. `reference dossier` -> curated per-template package under `research/external-templates/reference-library/dossiers/`
4. `generated research artifacts` -> committed JSON/embeddings in `src/lib/gen/template-library/` and scaffold research JSON
5. `runtime scaffold` -> internal starter used directly by generation

### Build method (`BuildMethod`)

How the user entered the builder. One of:
`wizard` | `category` | `audit` | `freeform` | `kostnadsfri`

### Build intent (`BuildIntent`)

What the user wants to build:
- `website` - standard multi-page website (default)
- `app` - interactive app with logic/flows
- `template` - compact 1-2 page template

### Internal theme vs Figma vs v0 design system

These concepts are also different and should NOT be mixed:

| Term | Variable/type name | Meaning | Scope |
|------|--------------------|---------|-------|
| **Internal theme preset** | `designTheme` / `themeColors` | Sajtmaskin's own theme preset and derived semantic colors used to steer the own engine's output. | Internal builder + own engine |
| **Figma reference** | attachment with `purpose: "figma-reference"` | A visual reference used to guide hierarchy, spacing, composition, and styling. Not a reusable component system by itself. | Prompt/reference concept |
| **v0 Design System** | `designSystemId` / `v0DesignSystemId` | External registry-backed design system consumed by v0. Tokens/components/registry concept, separate from our own theme presets. | External v0 integration |

Preferred terminology:
- Say **`designTheme`** or **`theme preset`** for Sajtmaskin's internal theme choice
- Say **`Figma reference`** for linked/imported Figma used as visual inspiration
- Say **`v0 design system`** or **`external design system`** for registry-backed `designSystemId`

Important rule:
- Do NOT call `designTheme` a `design system` without qualifier
- Do NOT describe a Figma file as if it were the same thing as a registry-backed `designSystemId`
- When needed in code discussions, prefer `v0DesignSystemId` as the clearer name for the external concept

### Project

A sajtmaskin project that groups chats, versions, and deployments together.
Stored in our database. Has an `appProjectId` (ours) and optionally a
`v0ProjectId` (on v0's side).

### Chat

A conversation with v0. Each chat produces versions. Mapped to a v0 chat ID.

### Version

A snapshot of generated code from a single v0 response. Has a `demoUrl`
(live preview on v0's servers) and files (the actual React/Next.js code).

### demoUrl

A temporary preview URL returned by v0 Platform API after code generation.
Hosted on `*.vusercontent.net`. Used directly in the builder's iframe preview.
Not the same as a deployed site.

### Deployment

When the user clicks "Deploy", we:
1. Fetch the version's files from v0
2. Process images (upload to Vercel Blob if needed)
3. Create a Vercel deployment via Vercel REST API
4. Return a permanent URL on the user's Vercel project

## Preview: why iframe and not always sandboxed?

The builder preview uses a plain **iframe** with the v0 `demoUrl` as source.
This is fast and simple - v0 hosts the preview, no local build needed.

The **Sandbox** (`@vercel/sandbox` via `SandboxModal`) is a separate, manual
tool for running code in an isolated server environment. It exists because:

- The demoUrl preview is **read-only** - it shows what v0 generated but cannot
  run custom server logic, access env vars, or connect to databases
- Sandbox gives **full runtime control** - Node.js process, env vars, npm install
- Sandbox is slower to start and costs more resources

So the default flow is: demoUrl in iframe (instant, free, good enough for
visual preview). Sandbox is opt-in for when the user needs to test server-side
behavior before deploying.

After deployment, the site runs as a real Vercel deployment with full
server capabilities.

